The Vice President gave a speech at Living History Farms in Urbandale, Iowa, where he expressed gratitude for law enforcement and their service. He emphasized the importance of public safety and the administration's commitment to law and order. The Vice President also addressed the recent storms in the area and thanked law enforcement for their response. He criticized the movement to defund the police and highlighted the rise in crime in cities where defunding is being considered. The Vice President assured law enforcement officers that they have the support of the American people and the administration. He discussed the administration's efforts to improve educational opportunities for all Americans and their plans to reform policing, which include additional funding for training and support for law enforcement. The Vice President encouraged Americans to sign a pledge to support law enforcement and not defund the police. The event concluded with a call to action for citizens to reach out to their elected officials and voice their support for law enforcement.